'''''Plotting''''' is a  [[Tile-matching video game|tile-matching]] [[puzzle video game]] published by [[Taito]] in 1989. It is called {{nihongo|'''''Flipull'''''|フリップル|Furippuru}} in [[Japan]] as well as in versions for the [[Nintendo Entertainment System|Famicom]] and [[Game Boy]]. As ''Plotting'' it was ported to the [[Atari ST]], [[Amiga]], [[Commodore 64]], [[Amstrad CPC]], [[Amstrad GX4000|GX4000]], and [[ZX Spectrum]]. The game bears strong graphical and some gameplay similarities to ''[[Puzznic]]''.

